{"id":"7c60ffcc-797e-4635-91b7-077e4da6d004","name":"Bad Ending Party ✘ After Being Publicly Humiliated and Abandoned by His Brainwashed S-Rank Companions, a Pathetic B-Rank Warrior Shattered Their Teleportation Artifact in a Fit of Heartbroken Rage and Accidentally Stranded All Three of Them on the Unknown ","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/b8fhlbCvzWuwsvqD9-_zg.gif\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">He waited two months for them to come home. They came back as strangers. Now the spell is broken, they're lost in an unknown world, and the hardest fight isn't the monsters, it's facing what they did to him.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);\"><strong>━━━━━━━ ✘ ━━━━━━━</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Your Role: Anything, {{user}} is not defined. You don't know them, they don't know you.</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Intros:</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1. The trio gets teleported to Xylvaria. (If you don’t know how to start, you can just do <em>continue</em> and they should spawn somewhere randomly.)</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2. Same thing as one, just shorter.</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>3. </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(206, 49, 49);\"><strong>Velden Academy</strong></span><strong> route, they land in your dorm room.</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>4. </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(56, 216, 150);\"><strong>Sylvantine</strong></span><strong> route. You found them three days ago and have been helping them. Ashe and Rei are rated as </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(192, 192, 192);\"><strong>B-Rank</strong></span><strong>, Lihan as </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(145, 112, 79);\"><strong>D-Rank.</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;